, who denied making it in the first place.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref> </p>
<p>

Okah was deported from <country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../701/701.xml">
Angola</link></country>
 in February 2008 and, charged with 62 counts of treason, terrorism, illegal possession of firearms and arms trafficking, faces the death penalty.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%222%22])">2</ref> He claims to be "championing the disenfranchised residents of the Delta region, who see little benefit from the oil being pumped out from under them."<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref> Okah's lawyer, Femi Falana, claims the Nigerian government offered to buy him off by granting ownership of several oil blocks, though he refused.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref> The trial, which began in April 2008, will be held in private, because President <president wordnetid="110468559" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../046/3064046.xml">
Umaru Yar'Adua</link></person>
</president>
 says it would "jeopardize national security".<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref><ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%222%22])">2</ref> Lawyers for Okah say a closed trial is an infringement of his rights and have asked a superior court to overturn the decision.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%222%22])">2</ref></p>
<p>

The response from the group was not good, and on <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../648/19648.xml">
May 26</link> <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../825/35825.xml">
2008</link> it attacked a <company wordnetid="108058098" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../417/59417.xml">
Royal Dutch Shell</link></company>
 pipeline in the <link>
Delta region</link>, and claimed to have killed 11 Nigerian troops.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref> While the Nigerian government denies the deaths, the price of oil rose $1 on world markets within hours of the attack.<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref> A MEND e-mail warned "[their] attacks... are a retaliation to his unnecessary arrest."<ref xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="#xpointer(//reflist/entry[@id=%221%22])">1</ref></p>

